        <title>ansible | Cache SSH key to avoid password input each time</title>
        <link>http://localhost:1313/en/ops/ansible/ansible-%E7%BC%93%E5%AD%98ssh%E5%AF%86%E9%92%A5/</link>
        <pubDate>Tue, 26 Nov 2024 02:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
        
        <guid>http://localhost:1313/en/ops/ansible/ansible-%E7%BC%93%E5%AD%98ssh%E5%AF%86%E9%92%A5/</guid>
        <description>&lt;img src="http://localhost:1313/img/cover/ops_cover.jpg" alt="Featured image of post ansible | Cache SSH key to avoid password input each time" /&gt;&lt;h1 id=&#34;background&#34;&gt;Background
&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;When using Ansible, to avoid the need to enter the SSH password each time a task is executed, we can cache the SSH key.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1 id=&#34;caching-ssh-keys-with-ansible&#34;&gt;Caching SSH Keys with Ansible
&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Start the ssh-agent background program&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;eval &amp;ldquo;$(ssh-agent -s)&amp;rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol start=&#34;2&#34;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Add the key to ssh-add, only input the password once&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ssh-add ~/.ssh/xxx&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol start=&#34;3&#34;&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Verify if the key is successfully cached&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ssh-add -l&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
